.SH "NAME"
svc_reserve \- change the space reserved for the reply to a request\&.
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.HP \w'void\ svc_reserve('u
.BI "void svc_reserve(struct\ svc_rqst\ *\ " "rqstp" ", int\ " "space" ");"
.SH "ARGUMENTS"
.PP
\fIrqstp\fR
.RS 4
The request in question
.RE
.PP
\fIspace\fR
.RS 4
new max space to reserve
.RE
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.PP
Each request reserves some space on the output queue of the transport to make sure the reply fits\&. This function reduces that reserved space to be the amount of space used already, plus
\fIspace\fR\&.
